Simple CRUD Python FastAPI code integrating with Postgres
(Lint → Test → Build → Push → Deploy)

Docker:

✅    [Multicontainer Microservices: api & database]
    - Setup api in Dockerfile
        --> install all dependencies: pip install fastapi uvicorn sqlalchemy psycopg2-binary
        --> multi-stage Dockerfile to optimize image sizes

✅    - Setup api and postgres containers in compose.yaml
        - add api env variables
        - add postgres env variables: (user, password & db_name): same values used in api
        - add passwords in github secrets *

Github Actions:

    CI:
    
    [Trigger] on push & pull request:

✅      - (Job 1)
      Linting check: action tool --> ruff-action
        --> if linting fails don't tun tests

      - (Job 2) 
      [Unit Tests]
      run tests 
        -> if tests successful (above 80%) -->  merge code to main (setup manual approval button)
            --> docker image build
            --> scan docker images ---> tool: Trivy or Snyk
            --> push image to docker hub
                ----> use Git SHA method to tag image

        -> on tests failure (below 80%) --> no code merge; fail workflow

    
    CD:

    [Automated Deployment]
    SSH into VM using GitHub Actions and deploy image built

*** Refactor:
- safe password use (api, postgres, github)
- multi-stage Dockerfile: optimize image sizes

